<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9692501615686></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9692501615686><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9692501615686>RE: Few things...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9692501615686#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 12:09 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I also use charm to save lives. For example, if you see some idiot running and yelling for help, charm the mob that is on them. Instantly they are saved from being beat to a bloody pulp. Also charm can teach all those kill stealers a lesson. For instance if there is a wizard using his powerful dd's and stealing your mobs all you do is charm the mob! They will waste mana thinking they are killing it, when in fact it's your pet. Soon they are OOM and the charm will wear off. Then you can kill it for exp.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
