<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96713139813934></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96713139813934><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96713139813934>Soloing from 11-16?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96713139813934#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=380><span id=Scholar>Cubwynn</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>67 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 24th 11:36 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are many places touted as the "best" to solo for a certain range, but I think that this can be a highly individual preference. Currently, I have been soloing in Lesser Faydark at either of the two bandit camps in the western portion of the zone. The northern camp is a three spawn group. They somewhat frequently drop bronze weapons (rapiers, spears, dagger, main gauche), and will drop between 1sp to 4gp. I cast for a pet until I get one that is blue by two levels to even, buff it (and myself), and med to full. My memmed spells are Mesmerise, Root, Soothe, Tashan, Choke, Languid Pace, Gate, and a DD. Soothe 2 of the bandits (cast until you get the message "xxx seems less aggressive"), then pull the third with Languid Pace. When you are able to cast, try to get in a Root. Get close enough to the mob to that your pet starts fighting, then back up and cast Choke. Target your pet and med until the mob is dead or the pet drops to 40% health or less. If the pet is in trouble, stand and melee or (optionally) cast your DD. This is a very easy way to break the spawn.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even at level 16, experience is not that bad, and the loot is excellent (approximately 30-50pp for a night's work), including gems, jewelry, bronze, and lots of rusty weapons. Bind yourself in Kelethin so you can Gate to sell when heavily encumbered. Make sure you give your pet a weapon, as that will increase his damage output.<br><br>The Nybright group is done much the same way, but with 4 spawns the downtime is less. I would recommend Breeze if you're going to attempt to solo the sisters.<br><br>Hope this is hepful!<br><br>Cubwynn<br>Ordo Ursi Prismatus<br>Lanys T'vyl<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
