<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9671272149364></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9671272149364><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9671272149364>RE: Soloing and Skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9671272149364#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=353><span id=Sage>Tehom</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>135 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 24th 10:26 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Some suggestions for low level soloing. Pull with tashan - at that level, it can be a pretty big swing in resists. Whenever you can, get SoW on yourself, but more importantly, on your pet. Using fear, you can have a pet with Spirit of the Wolf on it catch them pretty handily. Your melee damage isn't trivial at this level, either - generally you'll be killing most things with your melee damage and your pet. I wouldn't bother with weakness and similar strength debuffing spells - they don't seem to do much, if anything, to npcs.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
