<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9675792471228></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9675792471228><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9675792471228>RE: Soloing and Skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=9675792471228#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 29th 4:00 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>That is correct, there are no "free" points.<br><br>The confusion here is that each skill begins at a skill level equal to the level at which it was gained.<br><br>An example: Research is available at level 16. If I put one point into it at 16, I start with a Research skill of 16. If I put a point into it at level 20, I still have a Research skill of 16.<br><br>So, if you wait until level 10 to start your jeweling skill, it will start at a skill level of 1 anyways, because that is the level at which it is first available.<br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>Meza, HIE ENC Torv<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
