<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96693782218999></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96693782218999><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96693782218999>Soloing in the Lake of Ill omens</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96693782218999#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 22nd 5:50 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>Hello all<br><br>My name is Ra-maal and I would like to pass some information on Soloing in the Lake of Ill omens. I have soloed there since lvl 22 and find that it is both simple and safe.<br><br> Once you zone in to the lake follow the right side of the lake till you see the guard tower for the fortress. Go just right and inland from the lake. This puts you on the zone line. The zone line is just behind the 3 trees that you see.<br><br>Once you are there it try to get a SoW but its not needed. Summon a pet and buff you and the pet. My normal spell are:<br><br>DD<br>DOT<br>any hast spell. (hot swap with root)<br>any stun spell<br>Combat speed Debuff<br>Str Debuff<br>Magic Debuff<br>Mez<br><br>Now that you are ready to pull. move out a little to the dirt road. On this road you will find lots of mobs to kill. From the left sides run Goblins from the right and the Sarank and in the middle area are Skelly's and kitty cats. Once you find a target. Mez debuff ( all of them ) get to the end of your casting range and Dot the mob to break the Mez. Now when u Dot it you don't have to be looking at it, it just need to be inrange. Once Mez has been broken or if the Mez was resited. Run back to the zone line area. Depending on if you can cast though hits, if not you can use runes or Berserker Strength as a damage shield, cast either your stun spell or your root spell and step back out of aggro range. Next is the fun part watch you pet and the mobs health, if your pet starts lossing start casting you DD spells and refresh your Dot as needed or jump in and melee a little. Make sure that you get the killing blow in to get the most EXP for the kill.<br><br> Once you are done fighting med up and if you got hurt cast illusion Troll for the regen effect. The best part about hunting here is that you'll get good buff for Breeze and you have the safty on a zone line not too far away.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;    May you never need the services of a Cleric<br><br>                        Ra<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
