<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96712785510921></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96712785510921><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96712785510921>RE: Soloing in the Lake of Ill omens</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96712785510921#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=353><span id=Sage>Tehom</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>135 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 24th 10:37 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I had different strategies that worked for my lower level enchanter fairly well in Lake of Ill Omen, around level 22 or so.<br><br>Get SoW on yourself and a pet. As spells, I suggest having root, fear, DD, dot, color flux/shift, languid pace, tashani, and mesmerize. In general, I would start off with a root - some of the npcs in the lake are SoW'd, and root cancels it. Once rooted, dot them, slow them if you're not at full health, and nuke until root breaks. Pull it, without letting it hit you (so your pet doesn't attack prematurely) to a safe place, without many roamers. Once they hit you, stun them, move away while your buttons are greyed, then fear when they ungrey. Nuke it while it runs to get it to the point where it begins to slow down - if it gets too far away, you might get roamers. Let your pet finish it. This is a little mana intensive, but I used it to minimize the damage I would take. Illusion:Troll nicely reduces downtime, and you should try to balance your meditate time and healing time so they're about even. Make sure to have an attack speed buff on your pet, like quickness or alacrity.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
