	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a player who has had multiple enchanters on various servers, I have come across one immutable observations:&nbsp;&nbsp;Our pets are retarded.  If you summon a pet in a dungeon, you are asking for trouble, because if you don't stop to look back at where your pet is every 10 feet or so, it WILL train you.  No questions asked.  Enchanter pets are meant for one thing and one thing alone:  keeping the enchanter alive once he has set up camp.  Our pets can do as much damage as any necro pet, and as often as not can out-taunt one.  Problem is, they have only 1/3 of the hp a necro pet does, if that, and won't do anything until his master is in danger.  That makes a chanter pet good for one thing: pulling a frenzied mob off the chanter, if only for a single attack, that's enough time to cast a stun, a root, or a mez and get out.  To all new enchanters, please heed my warning:  your pet is not a pet, it is a security device.  It won't sit or roll over or play fetch, or even go for a walk, all it does is keep you relatively safe in the way only a brainless automation can.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
