	   <tr><td colspan=2>While the above poster is correct in that using posts is dangerous, I believe it is foolhardy to think that our pets only serve to taunt things off of us.<br><br>Pets are for grinds in dungeons.<br><br>There are times in dungeons where your group will get consistent 1-pulls; basically, after you have broken the spawn up sufficiently of where you are camping, and everything around you. It's during this time many enchanters become fairly listless, and I've seen many waste their party's time by turning into 2nd-rate wizards. This is when you make a pet. You can significantly speed up grinds like this, -provided- your party knows how to work around the often fickle targetting of the pet, and you don't let it roam. If you're a good player, your pet should never attract a train. Throwing away free damage from pets, in situations where they're perfectly safe to use, is very inefficient.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
