<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96661053617188></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96661053617188><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96661053617188>General Info</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96661053617188#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=566><span id= >Prestochangeo</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 10:55 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.79]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a 38th Enchanter, I've found soloing quite difficult, but not impossible. Crowd control doesn't just apply to groups, it's very useful in soloing; for obvious reasons. I'll just throw out some memories of soloing and see if it helps in your journeys.<br><br>When I was in the low level 20's, I was advised to try the Rathe Mountains. I wandered about the area looking for a good spot that provided protection and the opportunity to solo. I found this spot right by the paladin camp, where pally's get their Armor of Ro quests. There is a small camp of orcs right on the same plateau with the Paladins, it should contain 3 spawns.<br><br>The fortunate circumstance of this, is that the paladins will be your guards to run to if anything goes wrong, which happens from time to time. The tactics you can employ here are all up to preference. The 1st goal is to "break" the spawn. Last thing you want to do is have to deal with all 3 of the beasties at once, I found that it was just easier to root, mez, enthrall, or even calm one of the orcs and train the other 2 to the Paladin camp. The pallys should kill them off for you.<br><br>Then you can proceed to go back and only have to deal with a single orc. The tactics are up to you..&nbsp;&nbsp; <br><br>1. make a pet and use him to fight along side with<br>2. use the root & nuke tactic.. or even mez nuke tactic..  have a stun prepared just in case.<br>3. ignore my "break" the spawn technique and just charm one and let it beat on his friend, while you mez the 3rd.<br><br>You always can run to the pally's for protection when anything goes wrong. Use your Color Flux and a few jumps to get away. Also consider having a rune on you, to avoud getting beat on too hard and fast.<br><br>This is just a smattering of what I did to get a couple easy levels in the 20's. I'll elaborate on some other levels later. I hope you enjoy.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
