<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96655711920876></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96655711920876><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96655711920876>Pets and EXPerience</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96655711920876#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=450><span id=Sage>Sparr</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>113 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 8:05 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If a single pet outdamages all the other people who did damage to something it will take its share of the experience as if it was an even member of the winning group.&nbsp;&nbsp;This means if you are soloing then you need to outdamage your pet or it will take half the experience on each kill.  When grouped this isnt really a problem as any decent group will always outdamage a single pet.  When grouped with multiple pets its even better because if two pets do even damage then all the caster has to do is 1 damage so that neither pet outdamaged everyone else (including the other pet).<br><br>PS: Im posting this in all the pet class forums<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
